# 0xone-assistant — build context exclusions. Phase 5d.
#
# The build context is the repo root (`docker build -f deploy/docker/Dockerfile .`).
# Anything not on this list ships to the daemon. The runtime stages COPY
# only `pyproject.toml`, `uv.lock`, and `src/` — but a fat context still
# wastes bandwidth + slows BuildKit cache hashing.

# VCS / virtualenv / Python build artifacts
.git
.venv
__pycache__
*.pyc
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
*.egg-info
build/
dist/

# Editor / OS
.idea
.vscode
.DS_Store

# Runtime data — must NEVER bake into image
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.log
scheduler-audit.log
memory-audit.log
.last_clean_exit
.daemon.pid
.coverage
htmlcov/

# Local state dirs (host XDG mirrors). Bind-mounts replace these at runtime.
.claude/
.local/
.config/

# Secrets — defense in depth (.gitignore should already exclude these,
# but a misconfigured local checkout could re-introduce them).
.env
.env.*
secrets.env
**/secrets.env
**/.env

# Plan / docs / scratch — large research artifacts; not needed in image.
plan/
docs/
scratch/

# Phase-irrelevant
node_modules/

# NOTE: tests/ intentionally NOT excluded. The Dockerfile's `test`
# target does `COPY tests/ ./tests/` — without it in the build context,
# the CI test job would either fail or silently produce an empty dir.
# tests/ is not COPY'd by the runtime stage, so it does not bloat the
# final image; only the test target re-uses it.
